# Theory

## What is State in React?

State is one of the most important concepts in React.

State is used to store information or data that can change during the execution of an application.

Examples of data that can be managed using State include:

- Counter values
- User input
- Login status
- Selected items
- Form data
- Loading status
- Modal visibility
- Theme settings

When the State changes, React automatically re-renders the component and updates the user interface.

For example:

```text
Initial State
     ↓
User Performs an Action
     ↓
State Changes
     ↓
React Re-renders the Component
     ↓
Updated UI is Displayed
